The retained pBridge inventory shows that all four dHub channels and all
eight HBO queues are idle. Their inherited producer and consumer pointers
also match Valve's four-channel FIFO allocation, but the configuration
registers are write-only and cannot be verified directly.

Initialize that known layout explicitly before continuing the existing PIO
identification probe. Refuse initialization if any dHub or HBO activity is
visible, stop and clear every queue, and bound the clear wait to 100 ms.
Configure Valve's FIFO bases and depths, 32-byte channel MTUs and BCM base.
Also configure the nine depth-one semaphores used by the vendor NFC path.
Report the complete state both before and after initialization.

This remains an initialization-only milestone. It does not touch pBridge
TCM, enable a completion interrupt, submit a descriptor, transfer NAND page
data, enable DMA or register an MTD.

